node.text:
Dear quarantine, 
I had read about you in books and dictionaries, but I didn’t know you were for real.
Firstly, hats off to you - you were the one who made it possible for this fast moving world to pause, like literally! 

Travel plans, job changes, academic aspirations - it all came to a standstill. 
No one knew how to welcome you, and no one could anticipate the duration of your stay. 

Now that we have met, in the scariest of times, I must admit, that I actually kinda dig you. 

You have helped me see a side of myself, that probably I knew existed, but always avoided.

But now, I begun to see things with a different lens, and these things are good... 
Now I can see clearly, who matters to me the most, and for whom I matter. 
In this unknown space created by you, have truly realised the meaning of actions speaking louder than word.. how, efforts matter more than wishes. 
I have understood that, it is not always necessary for me to understand the crux of whys and hows- I can just be happy with what I receive, and learn to make the most out of it.

I realised that not everything in life needs my attention.. it’s important to let go some things and certain people - because I needed it more than they did.. 

It is nice- this new perspective! 
Now that I have met you, MAYBE, I will come and meet you more often, when my vision again gets blurry with the fancies of the world.

Thanks for the new realisations, and the new me!
Credits: @dheeraj.c_

People who are lucky enough to find their passion may not get this. But not everyone is happy with what they do.

It is never too late. I don't know what to do or where to go. But all I know is that the path I am walking on currently, doesn't lead to the destination I want to reach.

If it doesn't make you happy, it shouldn't be in your life. But if it is essential to your quality of life, you learn to let go of your non-essential comforts.
